<subSubSection id="ADBB7558A252AB3E9BD4783FB2B5D37F" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" type="notes">
<paragraph id="A5F1F52739D317E59336FF5605E0ACB6" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F4CB3146A4D825103A0E50501708A155" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">
The presence of hairs on the lemmas in material treated as 
<normalizedToken id="3652672344196BC9A050D35EB859E9A2" originalValue="“multiradiat”">
&quot; 
<emphasis id="9A211ADB9137DEFA70C5317CF3093D86" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">multiradiat</emphasis>
&quot;
</normalizedToken>
is confused in the literature. 
<bibRefCitation id="E2519ECF07C4633471A47FD7CF4E50F6" author="Mill, RR" journalOrPublisher="Opera Biologica" pageId="22" pageNumber="91" refId="B39" refString="Mill, RR, 1985. Eremopoa, Nephelochloa, Catabrosella, Colpodium, Hyalopoa, Catabrosa, Paracolpodium. In: Davis PH (Ed.) Flora of Turkey and East Aegean Islands, Vol. 9. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, 486-501." title="Eremopoa, Nephelochloa, Catabrosella, Colpodium, Hyalopoa, Catabrosa, Paracolpodium. In: Davis PH (Ed.) Flora of Turkey and East Aegean Islands, Vol. 9. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, 486 - 501." year="1985">Mill (1985)</bibRefCitation>
indicates that 
<taxonomicName id="435FA6B90A61BCF832634BDE04E3B98A" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. multiradiata" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" rank="species" species="multiradiata">
<emphasis id="16D62A1F703C1F5916905186DB3D6176" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">E. multiradiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="78BBA590872D98FA0644EA7BD631C37E" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. persica" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="A8E7ECCD5097012BF3E30272A47ABF2A" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">E. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.s. have lemma keels hairy in the lower ⅓-
<normalizedToken id="0F4D86553C4C212939877D095BF5AE0D" originalValue="½">1/2</normalizedToken>
. We concur with 
<bibRefCitation id="64B10A18308E88D04FD69E66708CEFC3" author="Tzvelev, NN" journalOrPublisher="Botaniceski Zurnal (Moscow &amp; Leningrad)" pageId="23" pageNumber="92" refId="B67" refString="Tzvelev, NN, 1976. Zlaki SSSR. Nauka Publishers, Leningrad Section, Leningrad, 1-788 [English translation: 1983. Grasses of the Soviet Union, 2 vols. Amerind Publishing Co. New Delhi.]" title="Zlaki SSSR. Nauka Publishers, Leningrad Section, Leningrad, 1 - 788 [English translation: 1983. Grasses of the Soviet Union, 2 vols. Amerind Publishing Co. New Delhi.]" year="1976">Tzvelev (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, who keyed 
<taxonomicName id="ACEE8C0637A7C51B9F9DF33B90968E5F" authority="subsp. persica" family="Poaceae" genus="E." infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. persica" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" rank="species" species="persica" subspecies="persica">E. persica subsp. persica</taxonomicName>
as lemmas short pilose along the base of keel and marginal veins and subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="CA430E1ADC53A8E19F3055702F49DEC6" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" rank="species" species="multiradiata" subspecies="multiradiata">multiradiata</taxonomicName>
as lemmas glabrous or with a few solitary hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="31429A41A0BF2656F793B709538B4C16" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">
<bibRefCitation id="CB9DDAF3CC3CD260702E992F9A7724DC" author="Mill, RR" journalOrPublisher="Opera Biologica" pageId="22" pageNumber="91" refId="B39" refString="Mill, RR, 1985. Eremopoa, Nephelochloa, Catabrosella, Colpodium, Hyalopoa, Catabrosa, Paracolpodium. In: Davis PH (Ed.) Flora of Turkey and East Aegean Islands, Vol. 9. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, 486-501." title="Eremopoa, Nephelochloa, Catabrosella, Colpodium, Hyalopoa, Catabrosa, Paracolpodium. In: Davis PH (Ed.) Flora of Turkey and East Aegean Islands, Vol. 9. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, 486 - 501." year="1985">Mill (1985)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished his new species 
<taxonomicName id="3727043AACCF8555CCE4F2FEA741F968" authorityName="R. R. Mill" authorityYear="1985" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa mardinensis" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mardinensis">
<emphasis id="43E07AADBC980C84076F8957B4F44E02" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">Eremopoa mardinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="65FAA4375B66EF9F48AC8475965E3754" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. multiradiata" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" rank="species" species="multiradiata">
<emphasis id="4897C13E6180C0B6F6EEA3BC479EDD2A" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">E. multiradiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on its glabrous lemmas, 8-12-flowered spikelets and florets strongly divergent from the rachilla. However, subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="741B2ECB979A13752DA2750327CBAADB" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" rank="species" subspecies="multiradiata">multiradiata</taxonomicName>
also has glabrous lemmas (as noted above) and divergent florets (when spikelets are in flower) and its (4)5-9(10)-flowered spikelets overlap in number; therefore, we treat 
<taxonomicName id="A142B9746881D7B5A0C951688E2FA0FB" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. mardinensis" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" rank="species" species="mardinensis">
<emphasis id="649EBAF2FE4BD60A6F08C78BB83E9968" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">E. mardinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="04D09F9779D6FE1B35A60AEDD69DD80C" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. multiradiata" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" rank="species" species="multiradiata">
<emphasis id="86AB3967D9D79C534FAB887FC234230A" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">E. multiradiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The type material of 
<taxonomicName id="5FAA8BAF0960D836CDB3949355A10550" authorityName="Post" authorityYear="1897" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eragrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eragrostis barbeyi" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barbeyi">
<emphasis id="818B86C635C74A54B88AB390B406B76B" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">Eragrostis barbeyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is from the same place as 
<taxonomicName id="5B0F875A5824B96FE811D5A04FF28DD9" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. mardinensis" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" rank="species" species="mardinensis">
<emphasis id="44F23B1FB8FF9103F31F8FB0D43DFC10" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">E. mardinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is clearly the same form (spikelets many-flowered); 
<taxonomicName id="93E89B50A6214B2790F8E33283969AF5" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Nephelochloa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Nephelochloa tripolitana" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tripolitana">
<emphasis id="52CC8A3C835FC03E406A090DA79E5188" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">Nephelochloa tripolitana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with ca. 12-14-flowered spikelets, also appears to belong to this form. If 
<taxonomicName id="C16F3EDE8511F7972AFA4E85E91CC2BC" family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. mardinensis" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" rank="species" species="mardinensis">
<emphasis id="70B8A3F81017CFAFE0917D10669640FB" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">E. mardinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were accepted as a species, the basionym names 
<taxonomicName id="F1CA506C2C5ADB0A98C18AC8E8922D80" authorityName="Post" authorityYear="1897" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eragrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eragrostis barbeyi" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barbeyi">
<emphasis id="428C499FA8F324BD93850B5413AF76B1" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">Eragrostis barbeyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="CB9F9E20AD37B26F963C5188C1298EFD" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Nephelochloa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Nephelochloa tripolitana" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tripolitana">
<emphasis id="4DD91842EAB6957212A3EBA0B300C99D" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="86">Nephelochloa tripolitana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would have priority.
</paragraph>
